1) Garbage Collection is the mechanism provided by JVM, to clean out the Heap, so that new object can be created. 
2) It destroys the objects which are 'not in use' or eligible for 'garbage collection'
3) Any object is said to be eligible for garbage collection (GC) if there is no 'Reference variable' attached to it.
4) Reference Variable: 

   class Test
   {
   public static void main(String[] args)
   {
   Test t;
   }
   }